-- South African Growth Plan Has Too Much State Intervention, Bus. Day Says
-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 2010-12-03T04:58:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-03/s-africa-plan-has-too-much-state-intervention-bus-day-reports.html
A growth plan proposed for South
Africa’s economy by the country’s economic development ministry
has too much state intervention, Business Unity South Africa
said, according to Johannesburg’s Business Day.   The plan will deter investors and skilled workers, Jerry
Vilakazi, the chief executive officer of the group, South
Africa’s largest business organization, said, the newspaper
reported.    To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  